# Supabase Rules

## Clients

| Client | Use |
|--------|-----|
| Browser (anon key) | Client Components only when unavoidable |
| Server (cookies) | Server Components, Server Actions, Route Handlers |
| Service role | Webhooks, cron, admin mutations — **server-only** |

Never import service-role client into Client Components or expose in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.

## Auth

- Supabase Auth for email/password + password reset.
- Read session server-side: `createServerClient` with cookies.
- Middleware refreshes session.
- On signup: upsert `profiles` with `role: 'user'`.

## RLS Required On

- `profiles`, `video_progress`, `course_progress`
- `certificates`, `purchases`
- Any table users query directly

## RLS Policy Direction

- Users read/update own profile (limited fields).
- Users read/write own progress (via controlled server paths preferred).
- Users read own purchases and certificates.
- Admins: use service role server-side, not broad anon policies.

**RLS is not a substitute for application entitlement logic.**

## Migrations

- All schema changes in `supabase/migrations/`.
- Include RLS policies in same migration.
- UUID primary keys for internal records.
- `created_at`, `updated_at` on business tables.
- Soft archive (`status: archived`) over hard delete.

## Storage Buckets

| Bucket | Access |
|--------|--------|
| `product-files` | Private, signed URLs, purchaser-only |
| `product-images` | Public OK for covers |
| `certificate-files` | Private, owner + admin |
| `admin-uploads` | Private, admin-only |

**Do not store protected member videos in Supabase Storage.**

## Queries

- Use indexes on: `subscriptions.user_id`, `content_plan_access(plan_id, content_type, content_id)`, `video_progress(user_id, video_id)`.
- Paginate admin lists — never load all members/progress at once.
- Entitlement checks query local `subscriptions` + `content_plan_access`, not Stripe API.

## Stripe ID Storage

- `profiles.stripe_customer_id`
- `subscriptions.stripe_subscription_id`
- `plan_prices.stripe_price_id`
- `products.stripe_price_id`

Always validate IDs against local DB before creating checkout sessions.
